Lighthouse is a better than trendy Greek tapas restrauant but it's seriously over-priced. The interior atmosphere which we can't currently enjoy is somehow both nostalgic of glamorous restrauant/bars & modern in design. Very good feel. The outdoor tables are just making due with the situation.  They have interesting cocktails - but honestly I didn't really enjoy either of the ones I ordered.  Their iced drinks are not on the rocks - instead they seem whipped into too much crushed ice that just takes away the sensation of a cocktail - making them more like an unsweetened & alcoholic Italian ice.   Stick to the cocktails that are served straight up.  Fyi they are not afraid of pouring - all the drinks were strong. The mezze portions are quite small & while each is more interesting than your typical Greek restaurant, I am not convinced they were any better - except the eggplant which is great.  The ceviche is good but a bit too spicy - masking any real ability to enjoy the tuna. Service was excellent. Lighthouse makes a good date restrauant - especially when it is safe to eat indoors again but otherwise skip it.

I can’t say enough good things about this place from its service to its well seasoned and flavorful food. The service is WONDERFUL and the staff is all lovely-they have a pulse ! The pickle plate, oysters, and their sourdough are my FAV’S. Shout out to Kasia (hope I spelt it right), mama Nama, and Kendra ! Our interactions at both of my experiences dining at Lighthouse make my heart warm. Thank you for doing what you do SO WELL despite the circumstances in these times. See you soon!

Lighthouse the green Bar-Restaurant in Williamsburg, Brooklyn preserves the Ozone layer.  This the restaurant that continuously keeps the quality of the excellent  food being served to the table at affordable prices. Being “green” means that their operations are directed at  minimising the carbon footprint by using locally grown and produced agricultural products and striving to reduce the non-recyclable waste as much as possible. This is a place with welcoming, warm and personal service, owned and managed by a brother and a sister, who maintain homely, warm atmosphere to the customers and the employees. The menu is devised by a young Chef whose culinary abilities are exiting and well expressed at each of the menu’s variety of items. A place which gives a feeling of “ belonging” to whoever comes in, be it “just for a drink”, for a taste of excellent food, or both… I recommend it highly.
